{"cursor":"23010","size":15,"audio":[],"currentlang":"en","article":"\n{{Infobox writer \n| name = TomÃ¡s Carrasquilla Naranjo image = TomasCarrasquilla.jpg caption =\n| birth_date = birth_place = Santo Domingo, Antioquia, Colombia death_date =\n| death_place = MedellÃ­n, Antioquia, Colombia occupation = novelist, storyteller\n| and essayist nationality = Colombian language = Spanish education = University\n| of Antioquia awards = Cross of BoyacÃ¡ movement = Costumbrismo influences\n| = influenced = Fernando Gonzales Ochoa notableworks = SimÃ³n El Mago\n| (1890) La Marqueza de YolombÃ³ (1926)\n}}\n\n'TomÃ¡s Carrasquilla Naranjo' (1858 â 1940) was a Colombian writer who\nlived in the Antioquia region. He dedicated himself to very simple jobs: tailor,\nsecretary of a judge, storekeeper in a mine, and worker of the Ministry of\nPublic Works. He was an avid reader, and one of the most original Colombian\nliterary writers, greatly influencing the younger generation of his time and\nlater generations. Carrasquilla was little known in his time, according to\nFederico de OnÃ­s, a scholar of Carrasquilla's works.\nIt was only after 1936, when he was already 68 years old, when he was awarded\nwith the National Prize of Literature, that Carrasquilla got a national\nrecognition.\n\nThe Colombian civil wars of the second part of the 19th century prevented young\nCarrasquilla from continuing his studies at the University of Antioquia. A committed intellectual, Carrasquilla organized\ntertuliasâsocial gatherings to read books and discuss themâin his MedellÃ­n\nhouse. Many young writers and intellectuals of his time joined those tertulias;\nfrom that time he was called \"Maestro TomÃ¡s Carrasquilla.\" Among Carrasquilla's\nadmirers was Colombian philosopher Fernando GonzÃ¡lez Ochoa.\n\nDe OnÃ­s argues that Carrasquilla's work passed unknown in Colombia and abroad at\nthe time because he lived during two different periods of Latin American\nliterature: Costumbrismo and Romanticism, that had representatives like JosÃ©\nAsunciÃ³n Silva in Colombia, and the coming of Modernism as a reaction against\nCostumbrismo. As many classify the work of Carrasquilla as Costumbrist, so De\nOnÃ­s classifies him.\n","linknr":279,"url":"Tomás_Carrasquilla","recorded":1375075338,"links":["/w/index.php?title=Tom%C3%A1s_Carrasquilla&action=edit","/w/index.php?title=Tom%C3%A1s_Carrasquilla&action=edit","//bits.wikimedia.org/favicon/wikipedia.ico","/w/opensearch_desc.php","//en.wikipedia.org/w/api.php?action=rsd","//creativecommons.org/licenses/by-sa/3.0/","/w/index.php?title=Special:RecentChanges&feed=atom","//bits.wikimedia.org/en.wikipedia.org/load.php?debug=false&lang=en&modules=ext.gadget.DRN-wizard%2CReferenceTooltips%2Ccharinsert%2Cteahouse%7Cext.rtlcite%2Cwikihiero%7Cext.uls.nojs%7Cmediawiki.legacy.commonPrint%2Cshared%7Cmw.PopUpMediaTransform%7Cskins.vector&only=styles&skin=vector&*","//bits.wikimedia.org/en.wikipedia.org/load.php?debug=false&lang=en&modules=site&only=styles&skin=vector&*","//bits.wikimedia.org/en.wikipedia.org/load.php?debug=false&lang=en&modules=startup&only=scripts&skin=vector&*","//bits.wikimedia.org/geoiplookup","//meta.wikimedia.org","#mw-navigation","#p-search","/wiki/File:TomasCarrasquilla.jpg","//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/b/b6/TomasCarrasquilla.jpg/220px-TomasCarrasquilla.jpg","/wiki/Santo_Domingo,_Antioquia","/wiki/Colombia","/wiki/Medell%C3%ADn","/wiki/Antioquia","/wiki/Colombia","/wiki/Novelist","/wiki/Storytelling","/wiki/Essayist","/wiki/Colombia","/wiki/University_of_Antioquia","/wiki/Costumbrismo","/wiki/Colombian_military_decorations#Order_of_Boyaca_.28Orden_de_Boyac.C3.A1.29","/wiki/Fernando_Gonz%C3%A1lez_(writer)","/wiki/Colombia","/wiki/Antioquia","/w/index.php?title=Federico_de_On%C3%ADs&action=edit&redlink=1","#cite_note-de_on.C3.ADs-1","#cite_note-De_On.C3.ADs_5-2","/wiki/History_of_Colombia","/wiki/University_of_Antioquia","#cite_note-udea-3","/wiki/Tertulia","/wiki/Medell%C3%ADn","/wiki/Ferna